15#ifndef DNS_ZT_H
16#define DNS_ZT_H 1
17
18/*! \file dns/zt.h */
19
20#include <stdbool.h>
21
22#include <isc/lang.h>
23
24#include <dns/types.h>
25
26#define DNS_ZTFIND_NOEXACT 0x01
27#define DNS_ZTFIND_MIRROR 0x02
28
29ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
30
31typedef isc_result_t
32(*dns_zt_allloaded_t)(void *arg);
33/*%<
34 * Method prototype: when all pending zone loads are complete,
35 * the zone table can inform the caller via a callback function with
36 * this signature.
37 */
38
39typedef isc_result_t
40(*dns_zt_zoneloaded_t)(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone, isc_task_t *task);
41/*%<
42 * Method prototype: when a zone finishes loading, the zt object
43 * can be informed via a callback function with this signature.
44 */
45
46isc_result_t
47dns_zt_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_zt_t **zt);
48/*%<
49 * Creates a new zone table.
50 *
51 * Requires:
52 * \li 'mctx' to be initialized.
53 *
54 * Returns:
55 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS on success.
56 * \li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
57 */
58
59isc_result_t
60dns_zt_mount(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone);
61/*%<
62 * Mounts the zone on the zone table.
63 *
64 * Requires:
65 * \li 'zt' to be valid
66 * \li 'zone' to be valid
67 *
68 * Returns:
69 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
70 * \li #ISC_R_EXISTS
71 * \li #ISC_R_NOSPACE
72 * \li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
73 */
74
75isc_result_t
76dns_zt_unmount(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone);
77/*%<
78 * Unmount the given zone from the table.
79 *
80 * Requires:
81 * 'zt' to be valid
82 * \li 'zone' to be valid
83 *
84 * Returns:
85 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
86 * \li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND
87 * \li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
88 */
89
90isc_result_t
91dns_zt_find(dns_zt_t *zt, const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int options,
92 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_zone_t **zone);
93/*%<
94 * Find the best match for 'name' in 'zt'. If foundname is non NULL
95 * then the name of the zone found is returned.
96 *
97 * Notes:
98 * \li If the DNS_ZTFIND_NOEXACT is set, the best partial match (if any)
99 * to 'name' will be returned.
100 *
101 * Requires:
102 * \li 'zt' to be valid
103 * \li 'name' to be valid
104 * \li 'foundname' to be initialized and associated with a fixedname or NULL
105 * \li 'zone' to be non NULL and '*zone' to be NULL
106 *
107 * Returns:
108 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
109 * \li #DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH
110 * \li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND
111 * \li #ISC_R_NOSPACE
112 */
113
114void
115dns_zt_detach(dns_zt_t **ztp);
116/*%<
117 * Detach the given zonetable, if the reference count goes to zero the
118 * zonetable will be freed. In either case 'ztp' is set to NULL.
119 *
120 * Requires:
121 * \li '*ztp' to be valid
122 */
123
124void
125dns_zt_flushanddetach(dns_zt_t **ztp);
126/*%<
127 * Detach the given zonetable, if the reference count goes to zero the
128 * zonetable will be flushed and then freed. In either case 'ztp' is
129 * set to NULL.
130 *
131 * Requires:
132 * \li '*ztp' to be valid
133 */
134
135void
136dns_zt_attach(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zt_t **ztp);
137/*%<
138 * Attach 'zt' to '*ztp'.
139 *
140 * Requires:
141 * \li 'zt' to be valid
142 * \li '*ztp' to be NULL
143 */
144
145isc_result_t
146dns_zt_load(dns_zt_t *zt, bool stop, bool newonly);
147
148isc_result_t
149dns_zt_asyncload(dns_zt_t *zt, bool newonly, dns_zt_allloaded_t alldone,
150 void *arg);
151/*%<
152 * Load all zones in the table. If 'stop' is true,
153 * stop on the first error and return it. If 'stop'
154 * is false, ignore errors.
155 *
156 * if newonly is set only zones that were never loaded are loaded.
157 * dns_zt_asyncload() loads zones asynchronously; when all
158 * zones in the zone table have finished loaded (or failed due
159 * to errors), the caller is informed by calling 'alldone'
160 * with an argument of 'arg'.
161 *
162 * Requires:
163 * \li 'zt' to be valid
164 */
165
166isc_result_t
167dns_zt_freezezones(dns_zt_t *zt, bool freeze);
168/*%<
169 * Freeze/thaw updates to master zones.
170 * Any pending updates will be flushed.
171 * Zones will be reloaded on thaw.
172 */
173
174isc_result_t
175dns_zt_apply(dns_zt_t *zt, bool stop, isc_result_t *sub,
176 isc_result_t (*action)(dns_zone_t *, void *), void *uap);
177/*%<
178 * Apply a given 'action' to all zone zones in the table.
179 * If 'stop' is 'true' then walking the zone tree will stop if
180 * 'action' does not return ISC_R_SUCCESS.
181 *
182 * Requires:
183 * \li 'zt' to be valid.
184 * \li 'action' to be non NULL.
185 *
186 * Returns:
187 * \li ISC_R_SUCCESS if action was applied to all nodes. If 'stop' is
188 * false and 'sub' is non NULL then the first error (if any)
189 * reported by 'action' is returned in '*sub';
190 * any error code from 'action'.
191 */
192
193bool
194dns_zt_loadspending(dns_zt_t *zt);
195/*%<
196 * Returns true if and only if there are zones still waiting to
197 * be loaded in zone table 'zt'.
198 *
199 * Requires:
200 * \li 'zt' to be valid.
201 */
202
203void
204dns_zt_setviewcommit(dns_zt_t *zt);
205/*%<
206 * Commit dns_zone_setview() calls previously made for all zones in this
207 * zone table.
208 *
209 * Requires:
210 *\li 'view' to be valid.
211 */
212
213void
214dns_zt_setviewrevert(dns_zt_t *zt);
215/*%<
216 * Revert dns_zone_setview() calls previously made for all zones in this
217 * zone table.
218 *
219 * Requires:
220 *\li 'view' to be valid.
221 */
222
223ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
224
225#endif /* DNS_ZT_H */
